Purpose
The Moon Starter Kit is the first RAMA system deployed to the lunar surface. Its job is brutally simple: collect raw lunar regolith into boxes and fire those boxes off the Moon using a tiny disposable rocket stage.

No mining.
No processing.
No infrastructure.
Just boxes up, gravity down.

This is the proof‑of‑system that starts everything.

Core Components
The Starter Kit consists of three machines, all designed to be cheap, disposable, and mechanically simple.

1. Lunar Sweeper (Straight‑Line, Disposable)
Function
The Sweeper’s only job is to:

Drive in a perfectly straight line

Sweep loose regolith forward

Fill a box

Seal it

Drop it

Repeat until it dies

Lifetime
Designed for ~50 boxes maximum

After that, it is considered spent hardware

No repairs, no maintenance, no return trip

Behavior
Moves in a straight line using simple traction

Carries a magazine of collapsed boxes

Automatically deploys a box when needed

Fills the box to target mass

Seals it mechanically

Pushes it out the back

Continues forward until battery depletion

Design Philosophy
Cheap

Disposable

Dust‑tolerant

No hydraulics

No fluids

No precision parts

The Sweeper is a broom with a motor, nothing more.

2. Regolith Collector (Crane + Arm/Gripper, Remote‑Controlled)
Purpose
This is the ONLY manipulator system on the Moon in Gen‑1.

Function
Drives to each sealed box dropped by the Sweeper

Uses a crane and arm/gripper to pick up the box

Loads the box into the rocket launcher cradle

Positions and aligns the box for launch

All operations are 100% remote‑controlled from Earth

Design
Simple tracked or wheeled base

One crane boom

One arm/gripper at the end

Cameras and lights for teleoperation

No autonomy required

Philosophy
Keep it simple

Keep it repairable

Keep it human‑directed

This is the lunar equivalent of a remote‑controlled forklift with a crane.

3. Gen‑1 Rocket Launcher (Disposable, Dumb‑On‑Purpose)
Purpose
Get a sealed regolith box off the Moon once.
That’s it.

System Description
A steel launch rail

A simple cradle

A disposable rocket motor bolted to each box

One ignition wire

One elevation angle

One job: throw the box upward hard enough for orbital capture

Why Rocket?
Because for Gen‑1:

It’s the cheapest

It’s the fastest

It’s the least exotic

It’s the most testable on Earth

It has the fewest moving parts

It requires zero lunar infrastructure

Failure Mode
If it blows up, you lose a box

If it misfires, you try again

If it works once, the system is proven

This is the lunar equivalent of a potato cannon with a guidance problem — and that’s exactly why it works.

Deployment
Delivered to the lunar surface in a single lander

Assembled and operated entirely by Earth‑based teleoperators

No MOEs, no astronauts, no EVA

Regolith boxes begin arriving in lunar orbit within days

Why This Matters
The Moon Starter Kit:

Proves the entire RAMA supply chain with the simplest possible hardware

Eliminates the need to launch bulk material from Earth

Enables RAMA to scale using lunar mass, not Earth mass

Creates the first closed‑loop between Moon and orbit

Allows factories on the RAMA Hub to begin producing structural components

This is the first real step toward a self‑expanding orbital infrastructure.
